Typography System
All text uses Material 3 type scale. Never set font size, weight, or family manually.

Use android:textAppearance with a ?attr/ token. Never use android:textSize directly.

Type scale reference:

displayLarge ?attr/textAppearanceDisplayLarge Hero text, marketing displayMedium ?attr/textAppearanceDisplayMedium Large emphasis text displaySmall ?attr/textAppearanceDisplaySmall Prominent text headlineLarge ?attr/textAppearanceHeadlineLarge Screen titles headlineMedium ?attr/textAppearanceHeadlineMedium Section headers headlineSmall ?attr/textAppearanceHeadlineSmall Sub-headers titleLarge ?attr/textAppearanceTitleLarge Toolbar titles titleMedium ?attr/textAppearanceTitleMedium List item titles titleSmall ?attr/textAppearanceTitleSmall Small labels bodyLarge ?attr/textAppearanceBodyLarge Primary body text bodyMedium ?attr/textAppearanceBodyMedium Secondary body text bodySmall ?attr/textAppearanceBodySmall Captions, hints labelLarge ?attr/textAppearanceLabelLarge Button labels labelMedium ?attr/textAppearanceLabelMedium Chip labels, tabs labelSmall ?attr/textAppearanceLabelSmall Overlines, badges

Usage:

<TextView
    android:textAppearance="?attr/textAppearanceBodyLarge"
    ... />

Color System
Semantic color attributes — always use these, never hardcode
Backgrounds: ?attr/colorSurface Main surface (backgrounds, cards) ?attr/colorSurfaceVariant Secondary surface (chips, text field fill) ?attr/colorSurfaceContainer Container backgrounds ?attr/colorSurfaceContainerHigh ?attr/colorSurfaceContainerLow ?attr/colorBackground Window background

Brand colors: ?attr/colorPrimary Primary actions, FAB, active states ?attr/colorOnPrimary Text and icons on primary ?attr/colorPrimaryContainer Tonal containers ?attr/colorOnPrimaryContainer Text and icons on primary container ?attr/colorSecondary Secondary actions ?attr/colorOnSecondary ?attr/colorSecondaryContainer ?attr/colorOnSecondaryContainer ?attr/colorTertiary Accent, highlights ?attr/colorOnTertiary ?attr/colorTertiaryContainer ?attr/colorOnTertiaryContainer

Status colors: ?attr/colorError Error states, destructive actions ?attr/colorOnError ?attr/colorErrorContainer ?attr/colorOnErrorContainer

Text and icon colors: ?attr/colorOnSurface Primary text and icons on surface ?attr/colorOnSurfaceVariant Secondary text, hints, captions

Outlines: ?attr/colorOutline Borders, dividers ?attr/colorOutlineVariant Subtle dividers

Never use in layout files: @color/white or @color/black @color/blue_500 or any palette color for semantic elements Any hex color directly @android:color/* for semantic elements

Layout Templates
Screen Root
Every screen starts with this structure.

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<androidx.coordinatorlayout.widget.CoordinatorLayout
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:fitsSystemWindows="true">
    <com.google.android.material.appbar.AppBarLayout
        android:id="@+id/appBarLayout"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:fitsSystemWindows="true">
        <com.google.android.material.appbar.MaterialToolbar
            android:id="@+id/toolbar"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="?attr/actionBarSize"
            app:title="@string/[screen]_title"
            app:navigationIcon="@drawable/ic_back_24"
            app:navigationContentDescription="@string/cd_navigate_back" />
    </com.google.android.material.appbar.AppBarLayout>
    <androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView
        android:id="@+id/scrollView"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        app:layout_behavior="@string/appbar_scrolling_view_behavior">
        <androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:paddingHorizontal="@dimen/screen_margin_horizontal"
            android:paddingBottom="@dimen/spacing_24">
            <!-- Screen content here -->
        </androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>
    </androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView>
</androidx.coordinatorlayout.widget.CoordinatorLayout>

Material Card
<com.google.android.material.card.MaterialCardView
    android:id="@+id/card[Name]"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    android:layout_marginTop="@dimen/spacing_8"
    android:clickable="true"
    android:focusable="true"
    app:cardCornerRadius="@dimen/radius_large"
    app:cardElevation="@dimen/elevation_card"
    app:strokeColor="?attr/colorOutlineVariant"
    app:strokeWidth="1dp"
    app:rippleColor="?attr/colorPrimary">
    <androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:padding="@dimen/spacing_16">
        <!-- Card content -->
    </androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>
</com.google.android.material.card.MaterialCardView>

Card style variants:

Elevated: cardElevation="@dimen/elevation_card", no stroke
Outlined: cardElevation="0dp", strokeWidth="1dp", strokeColor="?attr/colorOutlineVariant"
Tonal: cardBackgroundColor="?attr/colorPrimaryContainer"
