Accessibility Standards
Every layout must satisfy every rule below. These are not optional.

Every ImageView that conveys meaning must have android:contentDescription set to a descriptive string resource.

Every ImageView that is purely decorative must have: android:contentDescription="@null" android:importantForAccessibility="no"

Every icon-only button must have a contentDescription. The label must describe the action, not the icon (write "Share recording" not "Share icon").

Minimum touch target is 48dp by 48dp. Use android:minWidth and android:minHeight, or add padding to small icons to reach 48dp: A 24dp icon with 12dp padding on all sides achieves a 48dp tap area.

Use android:clickable="true" and android:focusable="true" together whenever making a non-button view interactive.

All text sizes must be in sp, never dp.

Layouts must not clip content at 200% font scale. Use scrollable containers for screens with dense content.

All directional attributes must use Start and End, never Left and Right: android:layout_marginStart not android:layout_marginLeft android:paddingEnd not android:paddingRight android:layout_gravity="start" not "left"

Text contrast ratio minimum: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for text 18sp or larger.

Focusable elements must appear in logical reading order: top to bottom, start to end.

Use android:labelFor to link a label TextView to its EditText.

Use android:hint on all text inputs — it becomes the TalkBack label.

Group related content using a container with contentDescription and mark children with android:importantForAccessibility="no" to avoid redundant announcements.

Test every screen with developer options Force RTL layout direction enabled.

Drawable Standards
All icons must be VectorDrawable. Never use PNG for icons.

Icon naming convention: ic_[semantic_name]_[size]dp.xml Examples: ic_add_24.xml, ic_delete_24.xml, ic_share_24.xml

Apply tint via android:tint or app:tint on the ImageView using a ?attr/ color token. Never modify the fillColor inside the vector file with a hardcoded color.

Directional icons (back arrow, chevron) must have android:autoMirrored="true" so they flip automatically in RTL layouts.

Use app:srcCompat (not android:src) when loading VectorDrawable via AppCompat.

Shape drawable (rounded rectangle):

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<shape xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android">
    <solid android:color="?attr/colorSurfaceVariant" />
    <corners android:radius="@dimen/radius_large" />
</shape>

Outlined shape:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<shape xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android">
    <solid android:color="@android:color/transparent" />
    <stroke android:width="1dp" android:color="?attr/colorOutline" />
    <corners android:radius="@dimen/radius_large" />
</shape>

Circle shape:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<shape xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:shape="oval">
    <solid android:color="?attr/colorPrimaryContainer" />
</shape>

