TextView tv[PascalName] tvTitle, tvSubtitle, tvErrorMessage ImageView iv[PascalName] ivAvatar, ivIcon, ivBanner MaterialButton btn[PascalName] btnSubmit, btnCancel, btnRetry TextInputEditText et[PascalName] etEmail, etPassword TextInputLayout til[PascalName] tilEmail, tilPassword RecyclerView rv[PascalName] rvRecordings, rvSearch ConstraintLayout layout[PascalName] layoutContent, layoutEmpty, layoutError LinearLayout layout[PascalName] layoutActions, layoutHeader MaterialCardView card[PascalName] cardRecording, cardProfile FAB fab[PascalName] fabAdd, fabRecord MaterialToolbar toolbar AppBarLayout appBarLayout NestedScrollView scrollView ViewStub stub[PascalName] stubError, stubEmpty

Performance Rules
Maximum view hierarchy depth is 5 levels. Flatten deeper structures with ConstraintLayout.

Use ConstraintLayout to eliminate nested LinearLayouts. Every nesting level adds an extra measure and layout pass.

Use include for repeated layout sections such as headers, footers, and state views.

Use merge as the root of included layouts to eliminate one wrapper view level:

<merge xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    tools:parentTag="LinearLayout">
    <!-- content -->
</merge>

Use ViewStub for layouts that are rarely shown — error states, empty states, onboarding overlays. The layout is not inflated until stub.inflate() is called:

<ViewStub
    android:id="@+id/stubError"
    android:inflatedId="@+id/layoutError"
    android:layout="@layout/layout_error_state"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent" />

Never use android:layout_weight inside a LinearLayout that is itself inside a ScrollView. This creates an infinite height conflict.

Never set match_parent height on a RecyclerView inside a ScrollView. The RecyclerView cannot measure its items and cannot recycle views. Use NestedScrollView with app:layout_behavior instead, or give the RecyclerView a fixed height.

RecyclerView items should have a fixed size where possible so the adapter can be configured with setHasFixedSize(true).

